  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(9) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "As a man astonied.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The word so rendered is not found elsewhere, but cognate words in Arabic have the meaning of being startled and perplexed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thou, O Lord, art in the midst of us.—After all, then, so the prophet’s reviving faith tells him, Jehovah is more than the passing guest. He abides still among His people. He is as a mighty man, strong to save, though as yet He refrains from action.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Thou, O Lord, art in the midst of us.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—After all, then, so the prophet’s reviving faith tells him, Jehovah is more than the passing guest. He abides still among His people. He is as a mighty man, strong to save, though as yet He refrains from action.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "We are called by thy name.—Literally, as in the margin, Thy name is called upon us, i.e. (as in Isaiah 4:1; Isaiah 63:19; Isaiah 65:1), “we are still recognised as Thine, the people of Jehovah.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "We are called by thy name.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, as in the margin, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Thy name is called upon us, i.e. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(as in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 4:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 63:19",
